
# Event Loop

### Explanation

- Event loop defines the process how the code is being executed
- Allows execution of non-blocking codes
- Makes Javascript asynchronous

### Execution process

- Heap (Memory)
- Stack (Execution)

### Queue

- Micro queue | Priority queue
- Macro queue   

#### Micro queue

- Micro queue is also known as priority queue
- Micro queue will consists of tasks such as API calls, promises etc
- Task in Micro queue will be pushed to main stack first

#### Macro queue

- Macro queue will consists of tasks such as timers, event handlers etc
- Task in Macro queue will be pushed to main stack once Micro queue is empty

#### Note

- time passed on setTimeout will not determine the start of execution, it is a minimum delay when it should be executed
